SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BYRON HAS APPLIED FOR AND RECEIVED A DETERMINATION LETTER FROM THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE ("IRS") TO BE TREATED AS A TAX EXEMPT ENTITY PURSUANT TO SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND DID NOT HAVE ANY UNRELATED BUSINESS INCOME FOR THE YEAR ENDED JUNE 30, 2018. DUE TO ITS TAX EXEMPT STATUS, BYRON IS NOT SUBJECT TO INCOME TAXES. BYRON IS REQUIRED TO FILE AND DOES FILE TAX RETURNS WITH THE IRS AND OTHER TAXING AUTHORITIES. ACCORDINGLY, THESE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS DO NOT REFLECT A PROVISION FOR INCOME TAXES, AND BYRON HAS NO OTHER TAX POSITIONS WHICH MUST BE CONSIDERED FOR DISCLOSURE. BYRON'S FORM 990, RETURN OF ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX, FOR THE TAX YEARS ENDING 2015, 2016, AND 2017 ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE IRS, GENERALLY FOR THREE YEARS AFTER THEY WERE FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE BOARD DELEGATES THE REVIEW OF THE FORM 990 TO THE AUDIT COMMITTEE. THE AUDIT COMMITTEE REVIEWS THE 990 AND REPORTS TO THE FULL BOARD ITS RECOMMENDATIONS AND THEN THE BOARD APPROVES THE 990.
